pr_title: Feature 37 Implement environment layer, add OIDC configuration, other cleanup
pr_body:
Closes #37 

1. Utilizes the dotenv packages present out of the box from create-react-app
2. Specifies a `.env` file for local environment variables
3. Adds a helper utility function that serves us the environment variables
4. If the flag "REACT_APP_local" is set to true, then all local environment variables will get picked from the .env file, but otherwise all environment variables set in the deployment containers will get picked up.

pr_title: Custom CI/CD pipeline replacing third party gh action
pr_body:
Closes #31 

Sets up CI/CD workflows:

1. Installs and builds the storybook
2. Takes the docs folder (where the static files are present) and explodes it into a branch called gh-pages (the repository configuration then allows GitHub to auto-deploy it)
3. Builds storybook for PRs

pr_title: Initial Setup of Storybook, React App, CICD deploy to GitHub pages
pr_body:
Initial Setup of:

1) Storybook (runs on port 6006)
2) React App (runs on port 3000)
3) CI CD configured for pushes to master, auto deploys to GitHub pages

Sample deployment (may require repo setting changes)

https://nimishbongale.github.io/webui/
